newsitem.title: EGYPT: Egypt overnight rates up, one-week unchanged.
newsitem.headline: Egypt overnight rates up, one-week unchanged.

text.p: Overnight interbank rates on the Egyptian pound rose on a slightly squeezed private market on Thursday to between 10 1/8 and 10 3/16 percent from Wednesday's range of 10 and 10 1/4 percent, bankers said.
"There were more takers today than usual for a Thursday -- the day before the weekend but there are no fundamental reasons for this squeeze," one banker said.
One week rates were unchanged at between 10 1/8 and 10 3/8 percent, the bankers added. Public sector banks continued to ask for a minimum 10 1/2 percent.
